Question 3 Answer

They are primarily used for whisking and chiffonade 

g.

Always ensure the blender is unplugged before cleaning and handling

h.

Question 18

Correct
Mark 6.00 out of 6.00
Flag question

Question text

Fill the Gaps:
Complete the following sentences about a digital thermometer:

 

Keep it clean before and after each use to avoid cross-contamination. Insert the probe into the  thickest  part of the food, avoiding bones or excessive fat. Wait for the temperature reading to  stabilise , then check the digital display to ensure it reaches the desired temperature for safe  consumption .  Avoid exposing the thermometer to direct heat sources and handle it with care when removing it from food. Clean the probe with warm, soapy water, avoiding submerging the  display , and store it in a safe, dry place away from extreme temperatures or moisture. Periodically check the thermometer's accuracy using recommended  calibration  methods. Replace  batteries  as needed and handle the thermometer with care to prevent damage or malfunctions

calibration consumption display stabilise batteries thickest

Feedback

Your answer is correct.

Question 20

Correct
Mark 10.00 out of 10.00
Flag question

Question text

Fill the Gaps:
Complete the following sentences regarding some of the safe use of workbenches and sinks:

 

Keep workbenches and sinks clean and free of debris at all times to help prevent  crosscontamination   and the spreading of bacteria as well as reduce the risk of  injury . Clean and  sanitise  work benches and sinks regularly, between job tasks, different food groups and at the end of the day. Ensure that workbenches and sinks are sturdy and stable before use. Make sure they are properly  secured  to the floor or wall to prevent them from tipping over or  moving  during use. Use cutting boards or other  protective  coverings on the workbench to prevent  scratches  or damage to the surface. Do not place or leave  sharp  or fragile objects in the sink such as  knives  or glass where they may be unseen by others and cause  injury .

secured protective moving injury crosscontamination  scratches injury sharp sanitise knives

Feedback

Your answer is correct.

Correct

Question text

Fill the Gaps
Complete the following sentence regarding industry standard handwashing procedures: 

 

Designated handwashing sinks should be properly installed and maintained throughout the kitchen.  They must be easily  accessible  and equipped with hot and cold  running  water. They must have a supply of liquid soap and single use paper towels. Staff should have access to the  SDS  sheets for the  hand  wash soap. Ensure that  signage  clearly indicates that the sink is for hand washing only and not food  preparation .

hand accessible SDS preparation running signage

Question text

Fill the Gaps:
Complete the following sentence regarding the safe use of tongs and serving utensils:

 

Use tongs or serving utensils to handle food instead of hands to prevent the spread of  germs  and bacteria. Use different  coloured  tongs or serving utensils for different  types  of food to prevent cross-contamination.  Use tongs or serving utensils with  insulated  handles to prevent  burns . Choose the right  size  and shape of tongs or serving utensils for the specific food being served or handled.

germs insulated coloured burns size types

Your answer is correct.

Question text

Select eight (8) safe operating practices and procedures when using disposable paper towels and cloth tea towels: 

Question 30 Answer
a.

Use separate tea towels for different tasks to avoid cross-contamination

b.

Wet tea towels are safe to use to take things out of the oven 

c.

Launder tea towels regularly and keep them clean.

d.

Used soiled tea towels should not be stored in the kitchen but in a segregated area

e.

Never use tea towels to wipe down surfaces that come into contact with food, such as cutting boards or food preparation surfaces

f.

Ensure that there is a bin readily available for the disposal of used paper towels and that it is emptied regularly

g.

Hand towels should be made from materials that are safe for in food preparation areas

h.

Replace tea towels frequently if they become wet or soiled

i.

Dispensers should be placed in convenient locations to promote hand hygiene and prevent cross-contamination 

j.

Keeps packs of paper towels next to the stove tops for easy access
